Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
setSelectedPtnCut(25.10)                              setSelectedPtnCut(25.10)

Name
       setSelectedPtnCut  - Sets the area and the name for the selected parti-
       tion cut area

Syntax
       setSelectedPtnCut

       [-help]

       <X1><Y1><X2><Y2>

       <PartitionName>

       Sets the area and the name for the selected partition cut area.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each setSelectedPtnCut parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man setSelectedPtnCut

       <X1><Y1><X2><Y2>
              Specifies the coordinates of the partition cut area.

       <PartitionName>
              Specifies the name of the partition cut area.

Related Information
              * setSelectedPtnFeedthrough

              * setSelectedPtnPinBlk

              * setSelectedPtnPinGuide

